 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,\mathsf {rx}_{\mathcal {A}}{x}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
. We shall refer to a univalent reflexive graph as a path object.

Let A be a contractible type with centre a. For any family of types B\colon  A \to  \mathsf {Type}, we may define a function \mathsf {ind}_{A,a}\colon  B a \to  \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
